# Architecture Rules

## Structure
- Feature-first monorepo: `packages/features/<name>/{presentation,domain,data}`
- Shared packages: `packages/{core,design_system,networking,persistence,analytics,routing,localization}`

## Dependency Direction
- presentation/ → domain/ (NEVER data/)
- domain/ → eddyscout_core only (NEVER presentation/ or data/)
- data/ → domain/ (for repository interfaces and entities)
- Features MUST NOT import from other features
- packages/* MUST NOT import from apps/*

## File Organization
- One public class per file (private helpers OK)
- Barrel files (package.dart) export only public API
- Generated files (*.g.dart, *.freezed.dart) colocated with source

## Layer Responsibilities
- **presentation**: Widgets, pages, view-model providers. No I/O.
- **domain**: Entities, repository interfaces, use cases. No framework deps.
- **data**: Data sources, DTOs, repository implementations. Handles I/O.
